Also Heal yourself as he nukes....you should be able to out heal his nukes, watch out for him using SoL (Shock of Lightning lvl 12 nearly irressitable PvP) to interrupt you.<br>
Depending on your lvl you should dot (swarm tyoe dot irressitable PvP) him too....obviously if you are 53+(not sure if you have updated your sig <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ) WD him which if he doesn't dispell should nearly kill him once you have dispelled him.<br>
Depending on your rules of combat....as long as you out heal him even if you both go OOM you can easily out melee him <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
The main rule for this fight is that you can heal the dmg he does you you where as any dmg you do he has to live with, so ware him down.<br>
<br>
Before the fight make sure you buff yourself fully.....cast crap buffs like STR, Firefist, Thorncoat first and then PR and DR (these don't matter against a wizzie!)... followed by See invis, Regen, FR, CR, SLN, SOW, MR<br>
You can change this buffage dependant on whether you are allowed to buff pre the fight...but I am assuming as the wizzie had a Skin he prebuffed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
If he does deside to dispell you to lower your resists and get rid of sow...then he has to get threw all the crap first.<br>
<br>
Also depending on the situation, if you have fought him before and he pumices your dots alot....then mem Harmony for the combat....cast this on him before doting him, means he has to dispell Harmony before he can get rid of the dot...every little helps!<br>
<br>
Good Luck...wizzie are a pest but Druids are the masters <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><BR>
Thebouy Ge'Zaire <BR>
