"When you inspect me ask yourself one question..... 'Do you feel lucky?' Well do you Punk!"</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthebouygezaire.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thebouy GeZaire</A> at: 8/9/01 5:20:51 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upeoni.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Peoni</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/9/01 9:50:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need specific advice on killing a wizzy.</span><hr size=1> How to win vs a wizard.<br>
<br>
In an arena battle where fleeing is not an option you should win every time with this method.<br>
<br>
If you're allowed to buff beforehand and be at full mana, buff in an order like this.<br>
<br>
2 instant cast items e.g.<br>
Jboots<br>
Telescope (made by tinker skill)<br>
see invis<br>
str<br>
resist poison<br>
resist disease<br>
thorncoat line<br>
circle of summer<br>
circle of winter<br>
resist magic<br>
Chloroplast<br>
Skin like nature<br>
<br>
That should just about cover you.<br>
<br>
As he removes 2 buffs, recast your jboots and telescope instantly (thus making his dispels much less effective)<br>
<br>
If there is just a 30 second buff period, i'd probably not bother buffing and save your mana, although you may want to throw up your instant cast buffs (if instant cast items are allowed), maybe see invis, endure magic, resist fire, resist cold.<br>
<br>
As another poster suggested, buy pumice stones, it saves the mana you'll use to dispel someone, and there is no recast time on pumice either.<br>
<br>
Essential item - ES arms or Velious armour bracer.<br>
If he's around the same level as you, he has ice comet, but no lure spells - so stack up on CR gear and try and get as much FR as you can - frog crown is a very good item, as are diamond mask/rings.<br>
<br>
Tactics.<br>
Heal his damage.<br>
Your heals are better and more mana efficient than his nukes, heal the damage he deals to you.<br>
<br>
Use your free casting arm dot to do damage to him until he is OOM.<br>
<br>
Just sit tight and heal the damage, as he has no where to run (i believe you said you're fighting in the arena), he will eventually run OOM and you should have at least some left (this will depend on how good your resists are).<br>
<br>
If your low on mana when he's oom, keep using your arm dot, and melee him to death, if he melee's you back (even tho you have more skill and will beat him anyway, you may want to cast thorns.)<br>
<br>
If you have quite alot of mana left, use ro's sundering to drop his FR, then let off a few nukes.<br>
<br>
Don't waste time on breath of ro or winged death if you level and get them, any good dueller will know to dispel these dots straight away. (besides breath of ro is very easily resisted)<br>
<br>
Peoni. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=leadar>Leadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(8/12/01 8:56:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovefrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Need specific advice on killing a wizzy.</span><hr size=1> Actually, there is ALOT of room to run around in the Arena.  You can run out of range easily.  <br>
<br>
1.  Immediately get out of range of wizard<br>
2.  Start casting you Creeping Crud line dot, hitting button as you inch towards wiz.  As soon as you are in casting range, they are in casting range of you too (but out of range of his roots).  Stay in that casting range (barely close enough to cast your dot on him), dont get close enough for him to root you. <br>
3.  Let him hit you with a DD from that range (or two).  Then run out of range, and heal yourself.  <br>
4.  Do this again, and again, till he doesnt cast on you anymore, (get him close to oom). <br>
5.  You will have about 2 bubs mana left when he goes oom(usually), because your heals are much more efficient than his DDs. <br>
6.  Move in and start meleeing wiz down, once he is oom or close to it. If you have enough mana left, dispell his skin, and then throw a dot on him while you are beating him down.  <br>
<br>
Spyder<br>
